S4.title: Study with me: Relax with light music and focus on studying on rainy day｜陪你讀書｜雨夜專注學習輕音樂陪伴 2025-05-27 16:43
S4.description:
Study with me: Relax with soothing music and concentrate on studying. Need a study partner? Let the simple, calming rhythm guide your attention. Whether you’re studying for an exam, working on a project, or just immersed in a book, this video creates a cozy study atmosphere with soft music and the sound of gentle rain. Put on your headphones and immerse yourself in this "Study with Me" course and let the rhythm keep you motivated and stress-free.
In this beautifully crafted ambient film, the rhythmic sound of rain blends perfectly with a minimal piano melody to create a sanctuary for your soul. Watch a studious girl, immersed in her book, become a silent partner in your productivity. Whether you're studying for a test, tackling a work project, or simply seeking a moment of peace, this video will transform your space into a cocoon of tranquility.

Scientific studies on auditory cognition reveal that natural sounds like rain activate the brain's default mode network, enhancing sustained attention. The audio design layers environmental details—a distant roll of thunder, the tactile rustle of pages turning—to replicate the sensation of studying by a window on a drizzly afternoon. The original soundtrack employs a deliberate tempo (60-70 BPM) aligned with the resting heart rate, using cello sustains to ground the listener, while subtle flute arpeggios add fleeting moments of uplift.

無論你是在趕報告、備考，還是想靜靜讀本書，這個空間裡只有書頁翻動聲與輕柔旋律。戴上耳機，讓溫暖的純音樂為你的學習時光注入平靜與動力。這不是一部普通的學習影片，而是一場「陪你讀書」的無聲陪伴，用輕快的節奏帶走壓力，用專注的氛圍點亮你的靈感✨

在綿密的雨聲與輕柔的純音樂交織中，這部影片為你打造一個獨特的沉浸式學習空間。鏡頭前的女孩專注於書頁之間，耳機隔絕外界紛擾，只剩下筆尖劃過紙張的細碎聲響與窗外雨滴的節奏。這不僅是一段學習實錄，更是一場心靈的陪伴——無論你是需要專注的學生、熬夜加班的職場人，還是單純渴望片刻安寧的靈魂，這部影片都能成為你書桌旁的「無聲夥伴」。
雨聲作為天然的白噪音，已被科學證實能提升大腦的專注力（參考學習心理學研究）。影片中刻意保留環境音的細膩層次——雨滴輕敲窗沿、遠處隱約的雷鳴、書頁翻動的沙沙聲——營造出「隔絕卻不孤單」的空間感。搭配原創的輕音樂，以鋼琴與弦樂為主調，節奏緩慢而穩定，避免過度起伏干擾思緒，卻又在副歌段落加入少量木管樂器的跳躍音階，暗示「學習中偶爾的小確幸」。

🌷Channel concept: 
I'm Venus! Let's have a productive study time together! We have live streams almost every day from 09:00 AM (GMT) for around 9 hours. If there's gonna be changes to the stream, I will let you know in advance through the posts. 
Let's encourage and motivate each other through our journeys and be supportive of each other. 
I'm so happy to get to know each one of you ! You are all my friends and a part of my family ✨🍀

🌷About me:

🍀What’s your name and how old are you?  HEYYY! I’m Venus (also Parnian) and I’m 23 (June 2001)
🍀Where are you from?  I’m Persian
🍀Where do you live?  And what are you studying ? I live in Budapest as an International medical student  (currently second year)
🍀How many languages can you speak?  I can fluently speak English and Persian/Farsi  (my mother tongue) I know some Hungarian and only a little Arabic
🍀What type of study sessions do you share?  It’s Pomodoro with 60 min study time and 10 min for break (in which we talk to each other )
🍀How often do you upload “Study With Me Livestream”?  Usually everyday unless something comes up and there would be changes in the schedule (which you can check the posts for it!) and in that case, I’ll let you know in advance 
🍀What time is the stream? usually around 9 AM (GMT).
🍀What apps do you use to go live and how do you communicate with people?  I use OBS to go live; my main platform is YouTube so check the community posts for the latest updates! (+ Instagram)
🍀What do you do when you feel sleepy?  I drink tea (coffee has no effect on me 😂) . Staying hydrated is very important. Do a little stretching or dancing, or change my location and go get some fresh air. 
🍀What are your hobbies? I usually play guitar or draw something as I enjoy both music and sketch 🎸🎨 I also like dancing and hanging out with friends
🍀What inspired you to start a “Study With Me” channel? I wanna make a lot of friends and create a motivational atmosphere both for me and for my friends (you guys😊✨)
🌸🌸🌸So let’s support each other and keep studying as we’re like each other’s family now and besties 🧚‍♀️✨

🌷 In a nutshell: 
Have to study myself because of big exams in the next time. Hope that these videos motivate yourself to get your own stuff done and that everything that you really want comes true.

🌷About chat: 
Please Be kind, respectful, No bullying or hate!
Encourage positivity, try to motivate each others to study!
No inappropriate questions or offensive language!
No spamming or self-promoting, Keep the chat clean!
Chat in English so everyone can understand!
Avoid discussing religion or politics to ensure a positive and inclusive environment for everyone!

✅How the bot works:
Every 45mins that you’re active (watching the stream without pause and also at least 1 message in the chat during this interval, which needs a trigger (using one of the commands)) it will give you 9 points! Just a gentle reminder, while it’s wonderful and competitive to collect points, the main goal is to study and go through our journey together!🩵✨

✅commands to use in the chat:
!start  to start counting your points
!starttask    when you wanna start your task (you also need to write the task at hand in front of it)
!finishtask     when you're done with your task
!info   how are the points counted
!points  you can see your points
!top     you can see the top 10 
!time to see how long the bot has been tracking you watching the stream (and hence your collected points)

S24.description:
📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

We have a Chat bot- 🤖
Commands for chat bot- 

!hi - when you join in👋
!start - to start studying
!top - Top Points
!points -  to know your points💯
!complete - when done with the goal

Chat rules:
- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!
- Please feel encouraged to write in English so no one would feel excluded in the chat :)
- Please check YouTube's Community Guidelines
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

S57.description:
Hi ^^ We’re Anne🐷 & Adrien🐭!
We’re a couple who met during our university years. We’ve always supported and motivated each other to study and work hard to reach our shared goal: getting into medical school. And this year, we finally made it! We are now in our first year of medical school.

Through our YouTube channel, we want to connect with new people, share our journey in higher education, motivate others to study—and even motivate ourselves. We know how hard it can be to sit down and get to work.
Sometimes you feel like it’s already too late to start. Or you avoid trying just so you can blame your failure on not working enough—telling yourself it’s not because you’re not smart, just that you didn’t try. Or maybe you’re scared it will be too hard, so you don’t even want to begin.

But we need to stop being afraid of failure. Everyone  ail at something at some point. What really matters is learning from your mistakes and trying again.
The real failure is choosing to stay down instead of getting back up.

💬 Q&A

Studies: 2 failed tentatives to get into Med School in France + engineering school (graduated), and now first year of Med School in Belgium

What is happening if your are not seeing us working while we should: getting a delivery, going to the bathroom or trying to kill bugs that are disturbing us
What do you like to do during your breaks:
 - both : usually we try to do house chores so we can have a real break afterwards and not distract too much so we can get back to work more easily and answers to messages in the chat

 - Adrien : play games

 - Adrien : really depends but either breakcore/dnb or ambiant sound
Who's the pig and who's the rat:
 - Anne : pig because she can eat anything with a refined palate, love the sun, and having naps under the tree shades
 - Adrien : rat because he belong to the sewer and is mischevious
What would you wish to become as professionals:

 - Adrien : neurologist

🎯 Chat Motivation
Feel free to share your study goals in detail for each session. Having a clear goal helps you stay organized, save time, and feel more motivated. Reaching your goals is super rewarding, so aim for goals that require effort but are still achievable.

🧠 Tips to Stay Focused

1. Start small
If you struggle to focus for more than 5 minutes, start with just 5. That’s already better than zero! Usually, the hardest part is just starting. So tell yourself you’ll work for 5 minutes—you might end up doing more, and if not, that’s totally okay. Start with 5 minutes of work and 10 minutes of break. Then increase slowly each day until you find the rhythm that works for you.

2. Set realistic goals
Plan your day with goals that are actually achievable. That feeling of success will motivate you to keep going—and maybe even push you to do a bit more. But always remember to keep it realistic. Feeling like you’ve failed can be very discouraging.

3. Talk to people during your breaks
Taking time to chat helps release pressure and puts things into perspective—like fears about falling behind or not being fast enough.
